   over the next decade, of which 12\% is currently funded. Incorporating
   threatened nonavian species increases this total to U. S. \$3.41 to
   \$4.76 billion annually. We estimate that protecting and effectively
   managing all terrestrial sites of global avian conservation significance
   (11,731 Important Bird Areas) would cost U. S. \$65.1 billion annually.
   Adding sites for other taxa increases this to U. S. \$76.1 billion
   annually. Meeting these targets will require conservation funding to
